data.title: Introduction to IBM Engineering Lifecycle Optimization Publishing
data.meta_description: The goal of the workshop is to provide participants knowledge on how to create reports using IBM Engineering Lifecycle Optimization Publishing
data.text:
A one-to-three-day workshop on IIBM Engineering Lifecycle Optimization Publishing (Rational Publishing Engine) that enables users to work with document templates generated from data from IBM products. The training provides users with a condensed knowledge of the tool itself in a practical way, so that they can start working and implementing requirements the very next day after the training at no additional cost. The workshop focused on practical knowledge transfer and examples prepared by the instructor or brought by the participants themselves.

The duration of the workshop is based on the agreed scope and can be adapted to the needs of the customer.

The goal of the workshop is to provide participants with the ability to create reports using IBM Engineering Lifecycle Optimization Publishing (Rational Publishing Engine) based on data from the IBM Engineering platform or other tools from the IBM portfolio.

Due to the workshop format of the training, participants can bring their problems or examples to discuss with the instructor.
